  "prompt": "What qualification do you need for a nursing job?",
  "response": "To become a nurse, you typically need to have a diploma, associate degree, or bachelor's degree in nursing from an accredited program. After completing your education, you must pass the National Council Licensure Examination (NCLEX-RN) to become a licensed registered nurse (RN). Some nursing positions may also require additional certifications or specialized training. Additionally, nurses are required to engage in continuing education to maintain their license and stay up-to-date with the latest developments in the field.",
